# Infrastructure as Code Patterns

This document defines standards for Terraform, Pulumi, and other IaC tooling. Follow these patterns for state management, module design, environment separation, and naming.

---

## Module Structure

### Directory Layout

```
infra/
  modules/
    vpc/           # Reusable network module
    eks/           # Kubernetes cluster module
    rds/           # Database module
  environments/
    dev/
      main.tf
      variables.tf
      terraform.tfvars
    staging/
    prod/
  shared/          # Shared config (e.g., provider versions)
```

### Module Design Principles

| Principle | Description | Example |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| Single responsibility | One module, one resource type or logical unit | vpc module only creates VPC, subnets, route tables |
| Explicit inputs | All configurable values are variables | No hardcoded region, CIDR, or instance types |
| Documented outputs | Outputs are documented with description | output "vpc_id" { description = "VPC ID for security group rules" } |
| Version pinning | Module sources use version constraints | source = "git::https://...?ref=v1.2.0" |

### Module Interface Example

```hcl
# modules/rds/main.tf
variable "environment" {
  type        = string
  description = "Environment name (dev, staging, prod)"
}

variable "instance_class" {
  type        = string
  description = "RDS instance class"
}

variable "allocated_storage" {
  type        = number
  description = "Storage in GB"
  validation {
    condition     = var.allocated_storage >= 20 && var.allocated_storage <= 1000
    error_message = "Storage must be between 20 and 1000 GB."
  }
}

output "endpoint" {
  value       = aws_db_instance.main.endpoint
  description = "RDS connection endpoint"
  sensitive   = true
}
```

