## State Management

### Backend Configuration

```hcl
# backend.tf
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket         = "myorg-terraform-state"
    key            = "environments/prod/terraform.tfstate"
    region         = "us-east-1"
    encrypt        = true
    dynamodb_table = "terraform-state-lock"
  }
}
```

### State Locking Checklist

- [ ] DynamoDB table (or equivalent) exists for state locking
- [ ] Lock is acquired before plan/apply
- [ ] Lock is released on success or failure
- [ ] No `-lock=false` in production scripts
- [ ] State file is never in version control

### State Security

| Control | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| Encryption | State encrypted at rest (S3 SSE, GCS KMS) |
| Access | Least privilege; prod state requires elevated role |
| Versioning | State bucket has versioning enabled |
| Backup | State history retained for recovery |

