## Secrets in IaC

### Never commit secrets

| Anti-Pattern | Correct Approach |
|--------------|------------------|
| Password in .tfvars | Use Vault, Secrets Manager, or SOPS |
| API key in variable default | Use environment variable or external data source |
| Private key in repo | Reference from secrets store |

### Secret Reference Pattern

```hcl
# Use data source to fetch secret at apply time
data "aws_secretsmanager_secret_version" "db_password" {
  secret_id = "prod/db/credentials"
}

resource "aws_db_instance" "main" {
  password = data.aws_secretsmanager_secret_version.db_password.secret_string
}
```

### Sensitive Outputs

```hcl
output "connection_string" {
  value     = "postgresql://${var.user}:${var.password}@${aws_db_instance.main.endpoint}/db"
  sensitive = true
}
```

