## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|-------------------|
| State in Git | Accidental commit, no locking | Remote backend (S3, GCS) |
| Secrets in code | Exposure in repo, audit failure | External secrets store |
| Monolithic root | Hard to test, slow apply | Modular structure |
| No state locking | Concurrent apply corruption | DynamoDB or equivalent |
| Hardcoded env values | Can't promote safely | Variables, tfvars |
| Destroy in automation | Accidental deletion | prevent_destroy lifecycle |
| No version pinning | Unpredictable upgrades | ref=v1.2.0 or version constraint |

---

## Validation Checklist

Before merging IaC changes:

- [ ] `terraform plan` (or equivalent) runs in CI
- [ ] Plan output reviewed for unexpected changes
- [ ] No secrets in plan output or logs
- [ ] Cost estimate included for new resources
- [ ] State backend is remote and locked
- [ ] Required tags present on new resources
- [ ] Module versions pinned
- [ ] Documentation updated for new modules
